{{Shrine |Name = Wadano Shrine |Image = {{ill|File:Wadano Jinja.JPG|ja|File:Wadano Jinja.JPG|lt=250px|lt_ja=250px}} |Location = {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京都}}{{ill|Ome City|ja|青梅市}}{{ill|Hinatawada|ja|日向和田}}2-317 |Coordinates = {{Coord|35|47|08.6|N|139|14|09.4|E|region:JP-13_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |EnshrinedDeities = {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|オオヤマツミ|lt=Great Mountain Deity|lt_ja=大山祇神}}、{{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|lt=Rock Long Princess|lt_ja=磐長比売神}}、{{ill|Kayano-hime|ja|カヤノヒメ|lt=Reed Princess|lt_ja=茅野比売神}} |Rank = |Founded = Unknown |MainHall = |AlternateName = |EmaAndOther = |AnnualFestival = |Ceremonies = |Map = {{Location map|Japan Tokyo|label=Wadano Shrine|float=center|relief=1|width=256}} }}
'''Wadano Shrine''' (和田乃神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社}} located at 2-317, {{ill|Hinatawada|ja|日向和田}}, {{ill|Ome City|ja|青梅市}}, {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京都}}<ref>After several municipal mergers, the current notation was adopted. Previously, it was located in {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県}} {{ill|Nishi-Tama District|ja|西多摩郡}} {{ill|Hinatawada Village|ja|日向和田村}}, in Kanagawa Prefecture, Nishi-Tama District, {{ill|Ome Town|ja|青梅町}} Hinatawada, and in {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京府}} Nishi-Tama District, {{ill|Ome Town|ja|青梅町}} Hinatawada</ref>.
== Overview == The enshrined deities are the three gods: {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|オオヤマツミ|lt=Great Mountain Deity|lt_ja=大山祇神}}, {{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|lt=Rock Long Princess|lt_ja=磐長比売神}}, and {{ill|Kayano-hime|ja|カヤノヒメ|lt=Reed Princess|lt_ja=茅野比売神}}. It was the head shrine of the former {{ill|Hinatawada Village|ja|日向和田村|lt=Wada Village|lt_ja=和田村}}. The nearest station is {{ill|JR East|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|lt=JR|lt_ja=JR}}{{ill|Ome Line|ja|青梅線}}{{ill|Miyanodaira Station|ja|宮ノ平駅}}, whose name is derived from this shrine. The annual festival is held on the first Sunday of September, featuring sumo wrestling dedicated by {{ill|Elementary School Students|ja|小学生}} and {{ill|Sumo Wrestling|ja|相撲}}.
== Surrounding Facilities, etc. == * {{ill|Tokyo Fire Department|ja|東京消防庁}}{{ill|Ome Fire Station|ja|青梅消防署}} Hinatawada Branch Office * Rinchuan Garden * {{ill|Meibakuin|ja|明白院}}: One of the Tama-Ome {{ill|Seven Lucky Gods|ja|七福神}}, enshrining {{ill|Fukurokuju|ja|福禄寿}}<ref>[http://ome7.tokyo/meibakuin/ Meibakuin Tama-Ome Seven Lucky Gods Tour]. Tama-Ome Seven Lucky Gods Association</ref> * {{ill|Hinatawada Nursery School|ja|日向和田保育園}}
