'''Wadano Shrine''' (和田乃神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located at 2-317, {{ill|Hinatawada|ja|日向和田|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Ome City|ja|青梅市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京都|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref>After several municipal mergers, the current notation was adopted. Previously, it was located in {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Nishi-Tama District|ja|西多摩郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Hinatawada Village|ja|日向和田村|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, in Kanagawa Prefecture, Nishi-Tama District, {{ill|Ome Town|ja|青梅町|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Hinatawada, and in {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京府|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Nishi-Tama District, {{ill|Ome Town|ja|青梅町|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Hinatawada</ref>.

== Overview ==
The enshrined deities are the three gods: {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|オオヤマツミ|1=Ōyamatsumi|lt=Great Mountain Deity|lt_ja=大山祇神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|1=Iwanaga-hime|lt=Rock Long Princess|lt_ja=磐長比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Kayano-hime|ja|カヤノヒメ|lt=Reed Princess|lt_ja=茅野比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
It was the head shrine of the former {{ill|Hinatawada Village|ja|日向和田村|lt=Wada Village|lt_ja=和田村|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
The nearest station is {{ill|JR East|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|lt=JR|lt_ja=JR|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{ill|Ome Line|ja|青梅線|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{ill|Miyanodaira Station|ja|宮ノ平駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, whose name is derived from this shrine.
The annual festival is held on the first Sunday of September, featuring sumo wrestling dedicated by {{ill|Elementary School Students|ja|小学生|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Sumo Wrestling|ja|相撲|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Surrounding Facilities, etc. ==
* {{ill|Tokyo Fire Department|ja|東京消防庁|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{ill|Ome Fire Station|ja|青梅消防署|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Hinatawada Branch Office
* Rinchuan Garden
* {{ill|Meibakuin|ja|明白院|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: One of the Tama-Ome {{ill|Seven Lucky Gods|ja|七福神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, enshrining {{ill|Fukurokuju|ja|福禄寿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref>[http://ome7.tokyo/meibakuin/ Meibakuin Tama-Ome Seven Lucky Gods Tour]. Tama-Ome Seven Lucky Gods Association</ref>
* {{ill|Hinatawada Nursery School|ja|日向和田保育園|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

