The nearest station is {{ill|JR East|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|lt=JR|lt_ja=JR|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/JR East|qq=}}{{ill|Ome Line|ja|青梅線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ome Line|qq=}}{{ill|Miyanodaira Station|ja|宮ノ平駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyanodaira Station|qq=}}, whose name is derived from this shrine.
The annual festival is held on the first Sunday of September, featuring sumo wrestling dedicated by {{ill|Elementary School Students|ja|小学生|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Elementary School Students|qq=}} and {{ill|Sumo Wrestling|ja|相撲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sumo Wrestling|qq=}}.

