'''Wadano Shrine''' (和田乃神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] located at 2-317, {{ill|Hinatawada|ja|日向和田|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinatawada|qq=}}, [[:en:Ōme, Tokyo|Ōme, Tokyo]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo Metropolis]]<ref>After several municipal mergers, the current notation was adopted. Previously, it was located in [[:en:Kanagawa Prefecture|Kanagawa Prefecture]] [[:en:Nishitama District, Tokyo|Nishi-Tama District]] {{ill|Hinatawada Village|ja|日向和田村|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinatawada Village|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, in Kanagawa Prefecture, Nishi-Tama District, {{ill|Ome Town|ja|青梅町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ome Town|qq=}} Hinatawada, and in [[:en:Tokyo Prefecture (1868–1943)|Tokyo Metropolis]] Nishi-Tama District, {{ill|Ome Town|ja|青梅町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ome Town|qq=}} Hinatawada</ref>.

== Overview ==
The enshrined deities are the three gods: [[:en:Ōyamatsumi|Great Mountain Deity]], [[:en:Iwanaga-hime|Rock Long Princess]], and [[:en:Kaya-no-hime|Reed Princess]].
It was the head shrine of the former {{ill|Hinatawada Village|ja|日向和田村|lt=Wada Village|lt_ja=和田村|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinatawada Village|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
The nearest station is [[:en:East Japan Railway Company|JR]][[:en:Ōme Line|Ome Line]][[:en:Miyanohira Station|Miyanodaira Station]], whose name is derived from this shrine.
The annual festival is held on the first Sunday of September, featuring sumo wrestling dedicated by {{ill|Elementary School Students|ja|小学生|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Elementary School Students|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 在籍者 (学習者)}} and [[:en:Sumo|Sumo Wrestling]].

